aWLICashValueProduct.Description: {\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1033\deflangfe1033{\fonttbl{\f0\fswiss\fprq2\fcharset0 Microsoft Sans Serif;}} {\colortbl ;\red153\green51\blue0;} \viewkind4\uc1\pard\nowidctlpar\lang2057\f0\fs16 Permanent life insurance coverage for as long as you live and continue to make timely premium payments.\par With level premiums and the accumulation of cash values, whole life insurance is a good choice for long-range goals. The guaranteed cash values can provide money later on to help with temporary needs or emergencies.\par \par \cf1\b\fs20 Features of Whole Life Insurance\par \cf0\b0\fs16\par Premiums generally are level and payable for life: Since premiums are level, the younger you are when you purchase a whole life policy, the less expensive the annual premiums will be.\par \par \b Dividends:\b0 Whole life insurance policies can earn dividends. Dividends result when our actual life insurance costs turn out to be less than we assumed in setting our premiums. Dividends are not guaranteed, since we don't know our actual costs in advance. \par \b Guaranteed Cash Values:\b0 Unlike term life insurance, which does not accumulate any cash values, some of the money you pay into your whole life policy accumulates as guaranteed cash values. If you choose to surrender the policy, these guaranteed cash values would be available to you. Or, as long as the policy is in force, you may borrow against them as a policy loan at the current policy loan interest rate. \par \par The amount of your guaranteed cash value depends on the kind of whole life policy you have, its size and how long you have had it. The growth in cash values is tax deferred under current federal income tax law. Borrowed amounts reduce the death benefit and cash surrender value. \par \par \par }
aWLICashValueProduct.Name: Standard Whole Life

aWLI_LifeIndividualProduct.Description: {\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1033{\fonttbl{\f0\fswiss\fcharset0 Arial;}{\f1\froman\fcharset0 Times New Roman;}} {\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;} \viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang2057\f0\fs16 The individual Life insurance provides a valuable death benefit \par to your beneficiaries upon your death.\par \par It's a permanent life insurance, which provides lifetime protection.\par \par The Individual Life insurance can be subscribed \b jointly\b0 or \b not\b0 .\par If jointly, you choose at subscription time when the beneficiary will receive money:\par \tab when the first person die, \par \tab or when the last person die.\par \cf0\f1\fs24\par }

aWLICashValueProduct.Description: {\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1036{\fonttbl{\f0\fswiss\fprq2\fcharset0 Microsoft Sans Serif;}{\f1\fnil MS Sans Serif;}{\f2\fnil\fcharset2 Symbol;}} {\colortbl ;\red128\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue0;} \viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang2057\f0\fs16 This allows you to convert a lump sum of money into an \cf1\b annuity\b0 \cf0 so that you can immediately \par receive income. Payments generally start about a month after you purchase the annuity. This \par type of annuity offers financial security in the form of income payments for the rest of your life. \par In other words, you cannot outlive it.\par \par \cf1\b Immediate annuities\cf0 \b0 allow you to:\par \pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720 Supplement your current income. If you are nearing retirement, you may consider \line transferring another savings or investment account into an immediate annuity. You \line can also move the proceeds from a deferred annuity into an immediate annuity.\par {\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Pay taxes only on the portion of your immediate annuity payments that is considered \line earnings. You are not taxed on the portion that is principal. The principal is the initial \line deposit made with funds that have already been taxed.\par \pard\par Like deferred annuities, immediate annuities can be fixed or variable. Fixed immediate annuity \par income payments are pegged to the amount you contribute, your age and the interest rate at \par the time of purchase. Those payments to you will not go up or down. \cf1\b Variable immediate \par annuity\b0 \cf0 payments vary with the investments you chose.\cf2\lang1036\f1\par }
